name: ebstv worldwide
description:
EBS TV is a privately held media company established in 2008 in Silver Spring, MD, USA to provide a niche transmission programming that targets the booming Ethiopian market globally. Since its formation EBS has been, and still is, providing its media to subscribers interested to access programming of Ethiopian history, culture lifestyle, sports, entertainment, tourism, and business.
EBS TV aims to promote Ethiopian and other African countries values, cultures and traditions globally. The much-needed information provided by EBS TV would help bridge the cultural divide and narrow the communication gap for Ethiopians residing in North America and around the world. EBS TV also envisions providing programs pertaining to the rich cultural heritage of Ethiopia, its history, tradition, socio-economic development, business, tourism and current affairs.

For More information on the EBS TV
EBS TV / Ethiopian Broadcasting Service

info@ebstv.tv
www.ebstv.tv

name: Teddy Afro
description:
Welcome to the official Teddy Afro YouTube channel. 

Tewodros Kassahun, better known by his stage name of Teddy Afro, is an iconic Ethiopian pop star who has dominated the national music scene for the last decade and a half.

Since signing with an Ethiopian record label in 2001, the Ethiopian music icon officially released albums are: Abugida (2001), Yasteseryal (2005), Yasteseryal Edition 2 (2005), Tikur Sew (2012) and Ethiopia (2017). His last album Ethiopia, became the most selling album of all times selling 600,000 copies on the day it was released. The album was also on top of billboard’s world music chart, #1 on CDBaby and Itunes album sells, which made it the first album in the nations history.                      

Enjoy! Subscribe!

name: Memeher Dr Zebene Lemma
description:
በስመ አብ ወወልድ ወመንፈስ ቅዱስ አሐዱ አምላክ አሜን።

የአብ ጸጋ የወልድ ቸርነት የመንፈሰ ቅዱስ ሕብረት አንድነት የእመቤታችን ምልጃ ከሁላችን ጋራ ይሁን።
ባላችሁበት ሁሉ ሰላመ እግዚአብሔር አይለያችሁ። አገራችንንም አለማችንንም ሰላም ያድርግልን።

ይህንን የዩቱብ ቻናል ለምትከታተሉ ሁሉ፡-
Memeher Dr Zebene Lemma በሚለው በዚህ ቻናል ላይ፡-

የኢትዮጵያ ኦርቶዶክስ ቤተ ክርስቲያን እምነትና ስርዓት ትምህርት ይሰጥበታል
የኢትዮጵያ ቤተ ክርስቲያን ታሪክ ይነገርበታል  
ትምህርተ ሃይማኖት፣ ነገረ ቅዱሳን ይሰበክበታል 
የመንፈሳዊ እድገት፣ ግብረገብነትና ስነምግባር ትምህርትና ምክር ይሰጥበታል 
እንዲሁም የኦርቶዶክስ ተዋህዶ ምሥጢር ይፈተትበታል።

በተለያዩ አርስተ ጉዳዮች ላይ:-
 
መንፈሳዊ እድገታችንን ከፍ ሊያደርጉ 
ተዋህዶ ሃይማኖታችንን ሊጠብቁ 
አልፎም አገራችን ኢትዮጵያን የበረከት ምድር ሊያደርጉ የሚችሉ መንፈሳዊ ትምህርቶች ታገኙበታላችሁ።
 
ስለዚህ 
ሰብስክራብ በማድረግ የደዉሉንም ምልክት በመጫን
 
በየእለቱ የሚሰጠው ትምህርት እንዲደርሳችሁ ማድረግ ትችላላችሁ።
ለሌሎች ወዳጅ ዘመዶችም በመንገርና በማካፈል ሁላችንም መንፈሳዊ ግዴታችንን እንድንወጣ በእግዚአብሔር ስም እንገልጻለን እንጋብዛለን።

የእግዚአብሔር ሰላም ከሁላችህን ጋር ይሁን።

Memeher Dr Zebene Lemma የሚለውን የዩቱብ ቻናል ሰብስክራብ በማድረግ ከእግዚአብሔር ጋር የሚያገናኙ መንፈሳዊ ትምህርቶች ማግኝት ይችላሉ።
የፌስቡክ ገጻችንንም ይጎብኙ ፎልሎውም ያድርጉን፡- https://www.facebook.com/MemeherDrZebeneLemma

ሰላም ለዓለም ሁሉ ይሁንልን አሜን!

name: Abby Lakew
description:
Welcome to the official Abby Lakew Ethiopian Music YouTube channel. 

Abby Lakew, is an African Grammy Award nominated singer songwriter and actress from Ethiopia and she was born in Gonder, Ethiopia. 

In 2007 she released her debut studio album ''Manale''. Which featured both English, amharic songs, Ethiopian traditional and dance music and was a reflection of her two identities – Ethiopian and American.

In 2012 she released a new single Shikorina followed by Endemewadeh, 2014 Abererew, 2015 the smash hit Yene Habesha and 2016 Befikir Eskista. 

In 2012 she landed the leading role in a critically acclaimed Ethiopian movie called Eyerus.

In September 2017 she released her second studio album ''Yene Habesha''.

In September 2020 she released a new single Messay.

description:

This show strives to address critical matters in the technology realm and bridge the huge information gap between the developed and the developing nations by bringing a new kind of TV program that can engage, educate, empower its viewers.

Solomon Kassa is an award-winning producer and host of the show. He also currently works as a senior IT consultant in one of the most respected Global Firm (fortune 500 company) in the United States. He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in computer programming and Master of Science degree in Information systems Technology from The George Washington University, a well-respected higher education institution in the United States.

name: Aster Aweke
description:
For more than 30 years, singer/songwriter Aster Aweke has been entertaining audiences across the globe. Her songs have become anthems to her fans in Ethiopia, as well as to Ethiopians living abroad, and she continues to win the hearts and minds of world music lovers. "Ewedihalehu" (I Love You), her 24th album, was produced with her longtime arranger, Abegasu Kibrework Shiota, and also features the work of exciting new music producers, Henock Negash, and Maru. This electrifying album is sure to delight long-time and new fans alike.

With the release of her many albums – including Aster, Kabu, Ebo, Aster Aweke Live in London, Hagerë, Sugar, Aster’s Ballads, Fikir, and Checheho – Aster has topped both the Billboard and College Music Journal’s (CMJ) specialist charts. Kabu reached and remained at the #1 position for four weeks on the CMJ New World music chart and was in the Top 10 for five consecutive charts (10 weeks) on Billboard’s World Music chart.

name: MO'AA TV
description:
Background Mo’aa is a television private broadcasting company. It is owned by Leadstar Media P.L.C. and licensed under the registration number KK/AA/1/0009407/2008 in the Ministry of Trade and Industry. 

Although preliminary discussion about the need to establish a television cable network began earlier, testing transmission started on December 14, 2016. After months of testing, Mo’aa started its actual regular transmission on April 16, 2017 – the Ethiopian Eastern day. Despite its short time preparation intervals from conceptualization to realization, it has become a media house that is being followed by millions in Ethiopia and beyond.

Afan Oromo is the media’s main medium of transmission. Speakers of this language are the direct audience of the television. Generally, its reach in content is holistic in which the central message focuses on the great commission – preaching and teaching the Gospel of Christ.

The primary objectives and purposes of ASRAT media is 
To report on news-worthy events of the Amhara in particular and of Ethiopia in general; to promote the history, identity, and culture of the Amhara people; to  provide platform for Amhara focused organizations to express their views, debate those views openly, and respond to questions from the Amhara people regarding those views; to report on discussions and meetings of the Amhara people in particular and Ethiopians in general as well as organizations and parties focused on the Amhara and Ethiopians; to report, document, and disseminate the inhumane treatments the Amhara people suffer under any circumstance to the Amhara people, to Ethiopians and to the international bodies.

This channel is dedicated to provide a platform where various perspectives are reflected on current, past, and future social, political, scientific, religious, economic, health, legal, historical, and cultural events and phenomena that affect East Africa; especially, our beloved homeland, Ethiopia, and her twin, sovereign and independent sister-nation, Eritrea.
Mehal Meda encourages civil, respectful, positive discourses and discussions as it serves as a venue for peoples of Ethiopian and Eritrean origins to share their opinions, frustrations, concerns, expectations, life-experiences, aspirations, hopes, and dreams.
Mehal Meda does not offer any professional advise, nor does it make claims of expertise in any general or particular area.

name: Ras-Samuel
description:
Ras-Samuel Welda’abzgi
Actor | Writer | Filmmaker
Ras-Samuel is an Actor, Writer and a vessel for telling stories that are gifted to him, and he is on a mission to share those gifts with the world.

He became an actor, writer to tell BIPOC stories in a creative landscape and on-screen because as a young African/Australian creative he always noticed the great inequality in terms of representation. He has worked as a consultant for an upcoming Netflix series. Ras-Samuel wrote, Produced and Starred in The Last supper, BLVCK GOLD, Found in a dream and Jebena Genie.  He appeared in Neighbors, Throbbin 84, Westermark effect and the Short film Breath

Ras-Samuel hopes to diversify Australia’s artistic landscape by inspiring the next generation who might not see many culturally diverse artists like him on stage and on screen.

name: Martie A Cooking ማርቲ ኤ
description:
Ethiopian foods are known for their tastes, looks and their delicious smell, bold, spicy, and savory flavors with plenty of options for meat and vegetarians (and vegans!) alike. There are no preservatives in Ethiopian cuisine, so almost most dishes are made fresh each day, and the way a restaurant prepares food is very similar to how families would make food at home. Popular dishes include Chicken stew called (Doro wot), Tibs (slices of beef pan-fried in onion and purified Ethiopian butter).  A distinctly Ethiopian blend of spices that might include cardamom, chili peppers, ginger, black pepper, and cinnamon),  
Ethiopian food is served on a large platter on injera, a sour, slightly spongy flatbread usually made from Teff, Ethiopian grain. Teff is packed with nutrients, a good source of protein, and is naturally gluten free.
Ethiopia is rich in it’s culture, tradition, natural resources, and has it’s unique food, which everyone in the world enjoy.
 Lots of love :)

Second purpose of Embilta Tigray is to educate Ethiopians all around the world on their culture. New generation Ethiopians born in the western world have lost their authentic culture. Third Purpose of this channel is to promote new talents from Tigray, Ethiopia. name: DJ Dalion
description:

My Education: In high school I studied hotel and restaurant, but at college I continued to study sound and video production. mostly I really loved to work with music. My interests in music have been there for as long as I can remember. I got my first keyboard from my mother when I was 13. as far as I remember it was the best gift I have ever received. Today I work as a Disk Jokey (DJ), Sound Technician, Promoter, youtuber and program leader for EABC (East African Broadcast).

description: Welcome to Bunna, a channel that blends personal development, mental health, entertainment, and coffee into one uplifting and inspiring experience. name: Geez City
description:
We are a group of artists, music producers, songwriters, sound engineers, promoters, and DJs. 

Collectively, we have created a fresh, unique, and authentic urban sound in Tigrinya, Amharic, English, and more, across different urban genres like hip hop, afrobeat, amapiano, dancehall, soul, and R&B, infused with a touch of Eritrean and Ethiopian traditional instruments.

Our goal at Geez City is to put East African urban music on the international music market, which we call Geez Music.

We come from a part of the world that has a rich history, land, traditions, and beautiful cultures that are thousands of years old and still thriving. We are one of the few in this world that have our own alphabet letters called Ge'ez, which is a sign that a great civilization has existed in East Africa since ancient times. We are here to use music as a means to communicate love, African progress, and creativity within ourselves and with the world.

Much love from The Creative Collective - GEEZ CITY

description:

ድምጺ ኣሜሪካ ሓደ ካብ ዓበይቲ ዓለምለኸ መሓውራት ዜና ኣሜሪካ ኮይኑ ዜናን ሓበሬታን ብ40 ቋንቋታት ን236.8 ሚልዮን ሰሙናዊ ሰማዕቲ ይበጽሕ:: ድምጺ ኣሜሪካ ትሕዝትኡ ብራድዮ: ቲቪን መርበብ ሓበሬታታትን ይዝርግሕ:: ትሕዝቶ ድምጺ ኣሜሪካ ብናይ ቴሌፎን ኣፕን ማሕበራዊ መራኸቢ ብዙሃንን’ውን ክርኸብ ይክኣል:: ብተወሳኺ ብሳተላይት: ብቴሌቭዥን  ማእከላይን ሓጺር ማዕበል ሬድዮ ይመሓላለፍ::

ድምጺ ኣሜሪካ ኣብ 1942 ዝምስረት ጀሚሩ ኩሉ መዓዝናዊ ሸፈነ ዘለዎ ሓቀኛ ሓበሬታ የመሓላልፍ:: ኣብ እዋን ካልኣይ ኹናት ዓለም:ዝሑል ኹናት: ኹናት ኣንጻር ግብረሽበራ ከምኡ’ውን ኣብ መላእ ዓለም ንዘሎ ቃልሲ ንናጽነት  ድምጺ ኣሜሪካ ኣብነት ናጽነት ፕረስ’ዩ::

ድምጺ ኣመሪካ ቋንቋ ትግርኛ መዓልታዊ ካብ 10:00-10:30  ወይ 4:00-4:30  ምሸት ብሬድዮ: ብሳተላይት: ብመርበብ ሓበሬታ: ፌስቡክን ዩቱብን ብቐጥታ ይፍነው::

name: ahadu media
description:
Welcome to Ahadu podcast, the podcast that's all about helping young people develop the mindset, skills, and strategies they need to succeed in life, relationships, and business.
Join our host Kirubel, as he/she shares insights, interviews, and advice from successful young entrepreneurs, thought leaders, and experts in their fields.
In each episode, we explore topics such as cultivating a success mindset, building and scaling successful startups, developing healthy relationships, and navigating the unique challenges and opportunities that come with being a young person in today's world.
Whether you're a young entrepreneur looking to start your own business, a student trying to figure out your career path, or just someone who wants to achieve more in life, this podcast will provide you with the inspiration and guidance you need to succeed.
So tune in, and let's explore the mindset, success, relationships, and startups that will help you become the best version of yourself.

name: Rafatoel Initiative
description: The Rafatoel Initiative is a revolutionary concept, designed to present the contribution of past Ethiopian civilizations through proven and backed evidence, documented globally. Examining their contribution in medicine, architecture, art, literature social development and much more. A strong Web-based approach will be implemented to inspire and educate with the oath to bringing back the ancient Ethiopian civilizations and wisdoms.  The Initiative will encourage millions of people in Ethiopia to unlock the hidden and unexplained and mystifying past of Ethiopia, to learn and become the future changers of this great nation.  The Initiative will strategically use social and digital media outlets to discovering the past along with written documents and various public gatherings. Historical and fundamental analyses along with international expert commentary of a verity of topics on untold stories and occurrence’s which have yet been explained.

name: KUKU SEBSIBE
description: This is the official YouTube Channel of the legendary Ethiopian singer Kuku Sebsibe. Kuku Sebsibe was born in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. She spent the majority of her education at Nazareth school and graduated from American Mission. Kuku's interest in music sprouted from a very young age. Since the age of nine, she used to entertain her classmates by mimicking all the popular artists of both Amharic and English music by using her lunch box as a drum. Her passion and love for music were nourished by her father, Dejazmach Sebsibe Shiberu's jam sessions at their home and his musical, peptic background. She lived in Washington, DC, United States for many years but moved back to Ethiopia c. 2003.

name: Living Beyond Breast Cancer
description:
Living Beyond Breast Cancer is a national nonprofit organization that seeks to create a world that understands there is more than one way to have breast cancer. To fulfill our mission of providing trusted information and a community of support, we offer on-demand emotional, practical, and evidence-based content that is meaningful to those newly diagnosed, in treatment, post-treatment, and living with metastatic disease.

For 30 years, Living Beyond Breast Cancer has imparted wisdom and connection via conferences, events, a peer-to-peer helpline, and more. Today, we remain committed to creating a culture of acceptance—where sharing the diversity of the lived experience of breast cancer fosters self-advocacy and hope.

Learn more at LBBC.ORG.

name: Ethiopian Press Agency የኢትዮጵያ ፕሬስ ድርጅት
description: Ethiopian Press Agency, established in 1940, is a public media enterprise operating in Ethiopia. It is the sole publisher of the only daily Amharic language newspaper known as “Addis Zemen.” The enterprise also publishes “The Ethiopian Herald”, a daily newspaper except on Mondays in English language. Among its tabloids are the weeklies: “Berissa”- in the local Affan Oromo; and “Al-Alem”- in the international Arabic languages. The agency has yet another newspaper in Tigrigna Language “Wegahita” and “Bakkalcho”in Sidamigna . By-monthly magazine, known as “Zemen” in Amharic also among the publications.

ETHIOPIA NEGE is a web resource of up to date news on Ethiopia. Its aim is to inform visitors on current affairs and scholarly presentations regarding social, economic and political issues that affect Ethiopia and her people.

Ethiopia Nege is also a portal for the dissemination of Ethiopian culture as it pertains to her religious belief systems as well as the developments in the secular sectors. The arts in cinema, music, poetry, painting and literary presentations can found in video, written and audio formats.

name: EtMDB
description:
Ethiopian Movie Database (EtMDB), the biggest movies, artists, cinemas and related company collection that helps Ethiopian movie enthusiast and movie lovers with unlimited Ethiopian movies, TV shows and Ethiopian artist contents.

EtMDB website offers a searchable database for Ethiopian movies, Ethiopian actors, actress, directors, writers, production and distribution companies and full movie crews.

description:
Hi, Welcome to Golden Ethiopian Music! This is among the channel for some Golden  Ethiopian Music with their Lyrics. We like to keep you entertained and solve lyrics mysteries for your favorite Ethiopian Songs. Subscribe for more Ethiopian Music, we feel like you need to enjoy!

Feel free to give us your comments, suggestions and requests, your feedback will  be my continuous improvement tool for my work.

Also don't forget to like and subscribe for more!

The special characteristic of Ethiopian music is the use of a five-note, pentatonic scale with large intervals between some of the notes. The music of the Ethiopian Highlands uses a fundamental modal system called “qignit”, the Ethiopian word for “scale”, of which there are four main modes: tezeta, bati, ambassel, and anchihoye.

name: Selah Ethiopia
description:
Selah serves Ethiopian women in and outside of Ethiopia by working to increase Biblical literacy and thereby encouraging and equipping for vulnerable, thought-provoking conversations around the Gospel of Jesus Christ, the mission of the Church, and the life of a Christian. Selah, a phrase mentioned in the Bible a handful of times, prompts the reader to stop and reflect. The Psalmist reminds us there is a relationship between praise, worship, and being reflective and still before the Lord. Our aim is to foster a sense of community by allowing a space for deeper and authentic reflection rooted in the Word of God. 

Selah hosts resources including articles, reflections, Bible studies, and devotionals in various media. The purpose of each and every content is to deepen our understanding of our faith and to encourage women to live every day with eternity in mind.

name: Sewmehon Films
description: Sewmehon films is an Ethiopian-owned entertainment, media, and production company. Sewmehon films is a content distribution platform dedicated to bringing the best in Ethiopian cinema to audiences all over the world. Through its website and YouTube channel, Sewmehon films distribute feature films, documentaries, television series, music videos, and short films from Ethiopia’s top film directors. It also hosts premier screenings of selected films throughout the year along with special events such as workshops and seminars. Currently,  Through these partnerships, it is able to reach a larger global audience. Sewmehon films are committed to supporting the growth of Ethiopian cinema through collaboration with local producers, industry professionals, and filmmakers from around the world. Its mission is to provide emerging filmmakers with access to resources that will help them showcase their work on a global stage.

description:
Redeeming Nations in Righteousness

Beza: (noun) Redemption in Ge’ez (an ancient south Semitic language of the Ethiopic branch).	 	   

Located in the heart of Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, BEZA is a vibrant international Church, where people from over 40 different nations come together to connect with God and one another. BEZA was started in 2006 to serve this vision: ‘Redeeming nations in righteousness’ by empowering people to impact others in all spheres of life through a lively relationship with God and cultivating biblical disciplines. We do this by creating an environment where anyone can experience the passionate love of Jesus! 

Over the past 15 years the church has grown from a small group that met in a family living room to approximately 2000 attendees every Sunday. We aim to be a place that you can call your home!

name: AradaTube Amharic
description:
This YouTube channel is dedicated to sharing my experience and knowledge in the field of information technology with my fellow countrymen. Information technology has become an integral part of our daily lives, and it has transformed the way we live and work. As technology continues to advance, we are discovering new ways to integrate it into our daily routines.

The primary objective of this channel is to help individuals overcome their daily IT challenges. I will be sharing tips, tricks, and advice on how to resolve common IT-related issues that we face in our daily lives. Additionally, I hope to inspire and encourage the youth to pursue a career in the IT industry.

Join me on this journey as we explore the exciting world of information technology together. I welcome your questions, requests, and comments, and I will do my best to respond to them in a timely manner.

Thank you for your interest, and let's learn and grow together in the world of IT.

name: Psych in Amharic with Tamiru Delelegn
description: I was born and grew up in eastern Ethiopia, Jijiga town. Got my B.Edand M.Ed in Pedagogical Sciences and Educational Psychology respectively from Bahir Dar university. I have been serving in BDU for the past 16 years. Teaching in class and surfing in the library have been the happiest settings of my life for many years. I was particularly "addicted" to teaching Personality Psychology. Got special interest for Ethiopian history too. I enjoy and value volunteering and working with students. I started this YouTube program believing that presenting lessons in mother-tongue/vernacular will improve learners understanding of psychological concepts and meet standards of access to quality education for all (for both campus-based and off-campus students).

name: Insight Ethiopia
description: Antoine Lindley is an award-winning American journalist and international documentary filmmaker; he has more than 20 years in the media industry and produced over 24 documentary films on Ethiopia. Antoine was producer and host of Ethiopian Television’s most popular English television documentary series “Insight with Antoine Lindley.” In collaboration with ETV, Antoine has produced vast documentaries promoting the positive image of Ethiopia globally. Antoine also has served as the Associate Press Officer for the Embassy of Ethiopia in the United States during 1998. He was presented with an award for in-depth reporting by the Illinois College Press Association in America in 1997. Antoine began his television career in on-air programming at BET Networks (U.S.A), a subsidiary of Viacom, the world’s leading branded entertainment company. Antoine Lindley currently resides in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.

Finfinne News Network was born out of the need to give a reliable voice to the Oromo people,the Oromo cause, and those who fight for the relalization of Oromo rights.

Independent Oromo political party leaders and Oromos who advocate for the Oromo's right were frequently denied voice and their voices where intentionally cut out from interviews. Finfinne News Network was born to fill the void and to be a voice for the Oromo people. All member Oromo media plege to serve the Oromo people and to be their voice.

Finfinne News Network n kan dhalate uummata Oromoo fi dhaabilee siyaasaa Oromoo walaba ta'aniif mirga Oromoof qabsaa'aniif sagalee ta'uuf. FNN n sabaa-himaalee Oromoo hedduu kan of keessaa qabuuf saba Oromoo tajaajiluuf of kenneera. FNN bira dhaabbachuun sagaleen saba keessanii ukkaamfamuu oolchaa.

name: זכרונות מאתיופיה-Memories of Ethiopia
description:
ארכיון מצולם של עדויות אישיות על חיי הקהילה היהודית באתיופיה. הפרויקט מתמקד כולו בחיי היהודים באתיופיה טרם עלייתם לישראל. באמצעות ראיונות אישיים נחשף פסיפס המרכיב את תמונת המסורות ודרכי החיים שנהלו בני הקהילה. 
הפרויקט נוסד והופק בעבור הדורות הבאים של בני הקהילה ובעבור כול מי שיחפוץ לדעת וללמוד על חיי הקהילה היהודית באתיופיה. תרבות שאיננה עוד.
הארכיון אינטרנטי, נגיש וחופשי לכולם. בכל מקום ובכל זמן. 
זה פרויקט פילנטרופי שיוסד על ידי קרן EV.

"Memories of Ethiopia" is a testimonial video archive depicting the lives of Jews in Ethiopia. It is aimed at preserving their cultural and historical heritage and making it accessible to present and future generations.  
 
The video archive includes in-depth testimonials and life stories of one hundred interviewees from twelve districts in Ethiopia. More than 175 hours of video recordings provide insight into the extraordinary lives of the Beta Israel in Ethiopia.

name: NUBIA The Path To Return
description:
Who Are We?

We are Unapologetic Africans, who, in the true spirit of Pan Africanism, have created this organization to assist in the healing and the restoration process of our people. We believe that all Africans must come together in the collective effort of setting up enriching programs necessary to bring our people back to their true home and true heritage.

We are Africans who believe that a collective sense of Pan-Africanism is of utmost importance to the survival of African communities, both on the continent, and around the world. We are Africans who still have faith in our people and who still believe in the promise made by the Creator to our people, which remains Truth to many survivors of the destroyed kingdoms of Africa: “That which is Lost, will be found, that which is stolen, will be returned, and that which is destroyed, will be rebuilt." 

For business inquiries, you may contact the Queen directly at TheQueen@NubiaReturn.com

description:
Holiness unto the Lord International Church (HUTLIC) is a non denominational full gospel church situated in West London. HUTLIC is a vibrant and multi-faceted church made up of congregants of Ethiopian and Eritrean origins.

The church was established following a heavenly mandate the founder and senior Pastor Zinaw Tesema received to shepherd God’s flock who, for many years, were scattered and burdened with heavy yokes that rendered them ineffective in their lives and ministries. God, in His divine sovereignty, filled Pastor Zinaw’s heart with zeal and compassion for the thousands of suffering Ethiopian and Eritrean Diaspora.

name: ECFCUK
description:
Welcome to the site of the Ethiopian Christian Fellowship Church in the UK.

We are pleased you have chosen to visit our site and hope you will find something refreshing and informative. Our goal, however, is not only to provide information but to also be an access point for the services of the Church. Ultimately though, our desire is to serve as instruments in helping all, but with emphasis on the Ethiopian and Eritrean communities in the UK, reach out to experience the Lord Jesus Christ for themselves! This is our ultimate desire for you as well – that you may know and experience Christ Jesus in His fullness be it His love, His forgiveness, His healing power or any element of His very life and person! He has come that we may have life and have it to the full! (John 10:10). May the Lord bless you richly.

name: Ethiopiawinet Dance crew
description: Welcome to the official channel of ethiopiawinet dance crew The 6-member Ethiopiawinet Cultural Dance Crew is one of the most popular dance groups in Ethiopia. Since their founding in 2009, they have won numerous national dance competitions including Balgeru Idol and performed in many music videos with popular Ethiopian singers. Ethiopiawinet specializes in traditional music and dances from Ethiopia, Eritrea, and across East Africa. Incorporating songs, dance, drumming and theatre, the group aspires to promote Ethiopian dance art and culture around the world. Exposed to diverse global dance forms, Ethiopiawinet remains grounded in deep and rich Ethiopian dance heritage and committed to sharing our heritage and its creative potential on world stages.

name: Jimma Tube
description:
CLICK HERE: 
#https://cutt.ly/ZrDlH47

Jimma is one of the zones of the Ethiopian Region of Oromia. Jimma is named for the former Kingdom of Jimma, which was absorbed into the former province of Kaffa in 1932. Jimma is bordered on the south by the Southern Nations, Nationalities and Peoples Region, the northwest by Illubabor, on the north by Misraq Welega, and on the northeast by Mirab Shewa; part of the boundary with Misraq Shewa is defined by the Gibe River. The highest point in this zone is Mount Maigudo (2,386 m). Towns and cities in Jimma include Agaro, Genet and Saqqa. The town of Jimma was separated from Jimma Zone and is a special zone now.

name: HuletLingo
description:
Hello! Welcome to HuletLingo! My name is Mel, and I'm an avid bookworm passionate about teaching Amharic and introducing Ethiopian culture to people like you! I started this channel with the idea of offering easy-to-follow videos for all Amharic learners, so whether you're a proficient Amharic speaker or a beginner, my videos have you covered! I create videos on various topics, from pronunciation to helpful conversation starters and daily conversations you might have with people. 
If you are like me, you're tired of seeing videos that are hard to follow and add unnecessary complexity to even the most straightforward concepts. If your goal is to introduce yourself in Amharic, and that should be what you should learn, not superfluous grammar rules. Plain and simple is sometimes the best route, and I've got you covered. Join me and subscribe for an immersive learning experience and take your skills to the next level!
If you need anything, I'll be happy to help if I can.

With Love, 
Mel

name: Think in Amharic
description:
Welcome to my channel! 

Think in Amharic is a YouTube channel where I teach basic Amharic. Anyone interested to learn Amharic is welcome. 

Learning a new language is a process, & it should be a fun journey.
So don't beat yourself up! 
To learn Amharic in a short time, teach yourself to think in Amharic.
Most foreigners, think in their native language first, then go on to translate what they want to say in Amharic. The problem is that the sentence structures are different in your language. That's the slowest way you can take to achieve Amharic fluency.

Start simple. Take baby steps. Stay consistent. Do not give up!



I upload 3 videos every week, please subscribe so you won't miss a lesson.
 
#learnamharic #learnamharicwithme #learnbasicamharic #amhariclanguage

name: Ethiopian Calligraphy
description:
ለምን ይህን አውድ ወይም ቻነል ተቀላቀልሁ?
እንደ ዛሬው የዲጂታል-አውቶማቲክ  የፅህፈትና የማስታወቂያ ፅህፈት ስራ ከመስፋፋቱ በፊት የፅህፈት ስራዎች የሚሰሩት በማንዋል ወይም በእጅ ስራ ነበር :: ያኔ ደህና የእጅ ፅሁፍ ያለው ባለሙያ ተፈልጎ እንዲፅፍ ይደረጋል ::  መፅሃፍም በእጃቸው የሚፅፉ ሰዎች እንደነበሩ ሰምቼያለሁ ::  በየሱቁ ግድግዳና ሰሌዳ ላይ ማስታወቂያ የሚፅፉ ሰዓሊዎች ብዙ ነበሩ :: 
ስለዚህ :  ይህንን  ቀደምት  የሆነ  ሙያ  በማሽን  ተተክቶ  ከሰው ልጅ  የእጅ-ጥበብነት  ከመወገዱ :  ወይም ከመዘንጋቱ  በፊት ባቅሜ መፍጨርጨርን  እና  ማስታወሻ  ማኖርን መረጥሁ ::

Calligraphy is the art of writing in a beautiful way. I just started working on Amharic calligraphy for beginners.

The other main concern of this channel is the learning of Amharic or English language. That’s mainly based on words we could use in daily basis and basic communicating words. 
This’s to say that we won’t limited in practicing calligraphy only but also we will see some other benefits from the language we gonna to learn. 

የአማርኛ ፊደል አቀማመጥ:: የቁም ፅህፈት:: ራፖር:: አማርኛ ቋንቋ ፊደላት እንዴት ይጣሉ ወይም ይቀመጡ?  

Winners don't do different things,
But they do things differently!

አሸናፊዎች የተለየ ነገር አይሰሩም
የሚሰሩትን ልዩ ያደርጋሉ!

Top Music  is a popular music genre that originated in the East Africa community & in the United States early 1990s. It combines elements of East African Culture music, rhythm and blues and jazz. Top music Ethiopia became popular for dancing and listening in the East Africa/Ethiopia ,where record labels such as Bini Bana Records and Shakura Studio  influential during the Civil Rights Movement. Top Music Ethiopia also became popular around the world, directly influencing Poletical music and the music of Africa.
According to the Culture music that arose out of the freedom of experience in America through the transmutation of gospel and rhythm  into a form of Hip Hop, secular testifying". Catchy rhythms, stressed by handclaps and extemporaneous body moves, are an important feature of Top music Ethiopia. name: Oyoegba Oyo
description:
"IBA OHUN DUDU OLODUMARE!!!"


"TRUTH crushed down(or stomped) to the ground, will RISE UP AGAIN!"                                                                                                  Ethiopian Proverb

"GOD crushed down(or stomped) to the ground, will RISE UP AGAIN!"
        Another version of same Proverb.

When WE(BLACK GODDESS/GODS) wake up to who WE ARE, break the chains of mental slavery, reclaim OURistory, and take back what has been STOLEN from US, then will WE asend back to OUR RIGHTFUL PLACE ON THE THRONE OF THE UNIVERSE!!!!

"As HE( ODUDUWA, AUSAR, HERU, YAHOUSHUA ) is now(On the THRONE) so are WE in this world."


OLODUMARE: "The HIGHEST, The ALMIGHTY, The I AM that I AM, The OM, The CREATOR and SOURCE of all that is!!!!" ...literal Yoruba definition is: "The Highest, the Most Exalted One from who I emanated and to whom I must return!"

*note: Olodumare is a Pre-Kemetian name of Amen-Ra


AMEN-RA: 'LIGHT shinning out of COMPLETE(PERFECT) BLACKNESS!"


AUSET: "The BLACKNESS of the vast un-manifest regions of existence!" (Female aspect of AMEN-RA)

AUSAR: "Lord of the PERFECT BLACK!!" (Male aspect of AMEN-RA)

HERU: "The union between AUSAR and AUSET! The union between SPIRIT and CREATION! GOD "made flesh", the "INCARNATION"! HERU is the "MANIFESTATION" of the GODDESS/GOD on earth! HERU is the "BLACK  WOMAN/MAN, GODDESS/GODS  on earth"!!!



ODUDUWA: "Exalted, Self Existent, BLACK ONE"

YAHOUSHUA: "Original name of Jesus"

*Note: Oduduwa is the original Pre-Kemetian KRST (Christ) figure, founder of Ile Ife (The Lost City of Atlantis) later identified as SUT, Tar, Ptah, Ausar, Heru, Krishna, Brahma, Shiva, Vishnu, Yahoushua, etc.
